# Cursor Rules for GameHub Project

## Git Flow and Branch Management
- NEVER add code directly to main branch
- ALWAYS create a branch using git flow structure (feature/, hotfix/, release/, etc.)
- NEVER merge code directly to main without user approval
- Always use descriptive branch names following git flow conventions

## Code Editing Preferences
- Always edit files directly without asking for confirmation
- Keep explanations minimal and only explain when specifically asked
- Focus on implementing solutions rather than discussing ideas unless requested
- Apply changes automatically without lengthy explanations

## Project-Specific Rules
- Follow existing code patterns and conventions in the project
- Maintain consistency with the current codebase structure
- Prioritize functionality over verbose explanations 